----------------
Small roll, lee slope, above average snow depth.

PROFILE
-------
Thick layer of new snow on hard thick crust, well consolidated due to sun. Basal layer slightly moist.

RUTSCHBLOCK
-----------
RB release when stepping onto it, but only below skis, some parts above did not fail.

CT and ECT show several failures in the new snow layer.

SNOW SURFACE
------------
New snow (about 20 cm), smooth, but in wind exposed areas no new snow at all, but hard surface (on sunny aspects) or strongly faceted surface layers in shady aspects.

SNOW DRIFT
----------
new small-medium sized wind slabs are forming.

ALARM SIGNS
-----------
none observed

AVALANCHES
----------
Observed small wind slab in the morning at 2100 m asl at Salezerhorn east ridge, time of release unkown.
Triggered small wind slab in the afternoon at Damm.

AVALANCHE DANGER
----------------
2 Moderate, above treeline, up to approx. 2400 m, above 3 Considerable,
Overall limited terrain covered and poor visibility. New snow accumulations by wind can be easily triggered, in all aspects, but fairly localized.</slf:text></slf:profiletext></slf:profiletext-list></caaml:customData></caaml:metaData><caaml:timeRef><caaml:recordTime><caaml:TimeInstant><caaml:timePosition>2015-02-24T12:00:00+01:00</caaml:timePosition></caaml:TimeInstant></caaml:recordTime><caaml:dateTimeReport>2015-02-24T17:09:56+01:00</caaml:dateTimeReport><caaml:dateTimeLastEdit>2024-12-30T16:25:47.812060+01:00</caaml:dateTimeLastEdit></caaml:timeRef><caaml:srcRef/><caaml:locRef><caaml:name>Davos - Salezer M&#228;der</caaml:name><caaml:validElevation><caaml:ElevationPosition uom="m"><caaml:position>2020</caaml:position></caaml:ElevationPosition></caaml:validElevation><caaml:validAspect><caaml:AspectPosition><caaml:position>SE</caaml:position></caaml:AspectPosition></caaml:validAspect><caaml:validSlopeAngle><caaml:SlopeAnglePosition uom="deg"><caaml:position>40</caaml:position></caaml:SlopeAnglePosition></caaml:validSlopeAngle><caaml:pointLocation><gml:Point id="pointID" srsName="urn:ogc:def:crs:OGC:1.3:CRS84" srsDimension="2"><gml:pos>9.837623 46.825168</gml:pos></gml:Point></caaml:pointLocation></caaml:locRef><caaml:snowProfileResultsOf><caaml:SnowProfileMeasurements dir="top down"><caaml:profileDepth uom="cm">138.0</caaml:profileDepth><caaml:weatherCond><caaml:airTempPres uom="degC">-5.5</caaml:airTempPres></caaml:weatherCond><caaml:snowPackCond><caaml:hS><caaml:Components><caaml:height uom="cm">138.0</caaml:height></caaml:Components></caaml:hS></caaml:snowPackCond><caaml:stratProfile><caaml:Layer><caaml:depthTop uom="cm">0.0</caaml:depthTop><caaml:thickness uom="cm">18.0</caaml:thickness><caaml:wetness uom="">D</caaml:wetness><caaml:grainFormPrimary>PP</caaml:grainFormPrimary><caaml:grainFormSecondary>DF</caaml:grainFormSecondary><caaml:grainSize uom="mm"><caaml:Components><caaml:avg>1.0</caaml:avg><caaml:avgMax>2.0</caaml:avgMax></caaml:Components></caaml:grain